Hi Sean,


I hope you're doing well. My name is Lexi, and I=E2=80=99m with Zintro=E2=
=80=94a platform
that connects professionals and subject matter experts with paid research
opportunities.


We=E2=80=99re currently conducting a study on Software Developer Tools and =
are
looking to speak with both experienced and aspiring software developers.
The goal is to better understand how developers select their tools, use
various Integrated Development Environments (IDEs), and approach technical
problem-solving. This is a 60-minute webcam interview.


Would you be open to participating? If so, please respond with the
following:


1. Which of the following IDEs have you used in the past few weeks or days?
(Select all that apply)


A. Cline

B. Cursor

C. Replit

D. Tabnine

E. Trae

F. Windsurf

G. None of the above


2. Participants typically quote $320 for this type of engagement. What is
your preferred rate for participating in a 60-minute interview on this
topic?


Let me know if you're interested, and I=E2=80=99ll be happy to provide more
details. I look forward to hearing from you!


Best Regards,


Lexi Pearson | Qualitative Research Manager

